Food tasted good. Very small portions. We went an hour before closing on Sunday 16th and the staff was not very welcoming. Did not call name/did not give enough plastic ware for amount of orders We were in a hotel and had to share a spoon. The soup portion was very small for price. Zucchini noodles were tasty and portions were ok for that dish.  Garlic bread was the best! It was amazingly good! We would probably eat here again if we lived here as the food was good. Just don’t expect friendliness and make sure you are specific if you need plastic ware.

I'm a commuter student from CR area and I couldn't leave my dog home alone. So I brought him with me to school and it's 95 degrees outside. Absolutely not will I leave him in the car! He is an ESA and this establishment was open to me and him staying and eating lunch. He was calm and stayed in the corner of a booth. Thank you so much for being so understanding ❤️

Excellent customer service at this Iowa City location. Their zucchini noodles are delicious and worth it.

I stayed in Iowa City for several weeks as my husband was a patient at the hospital.  He was suffering neurological issues and somewhere around the 2nd week mark, I was sick of hospital food so I grabbed food from Noodles and Co.  My husband remembers absolutely nothing from his 30 days there except for the noodles and co.  Their food is so horrendous that the memory is burned into his inflamed brain and sticks there to this day.  Thank you, Noodles and Co, for at least giving him one memory during an otherwise completely forgotten time frame.
